  "original_title": "Additional $ 25 Mn from Australia to Sri Lanka",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Additional $ 25 Mn from Australia to Sri Lanka",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "COLOMBO (News 1st): Australia will provide an additional $25 million to help Sri Lanka meet urgent food and healthcare needs, as it confronts its worst economic crisis in 70 years.",
        "During this challenging period, Australia stands with the people of Sri Lanka, especially those experiencing severe hardship, said Pat Conroy MP, Australian Minister for International Development and the Pacific.",
        "This additional support brings Australia\u2019s Official Development Assistance response to $75 million.",
        "\"Our support will be delivered through UN agencies to provide food, health and nutrition services, access to safe water and essential support for those at risk, including women and children,\" said Pat Conroy MP, Australian Minister for International Development and the Pacific.",
        "Australia\u2019s continued assistance to Sri Lanka supports our mutual interest in a secure and resilient Indian Ocean and reinforces our 75 year-strong relationship built on cooperation and community connection.",
        "The extra humanitarian assistance is in addition to the $23 million in ongoing development assistance to Sri Lanka in 2022-23."
      ],
